Both files emitted and the transcript validates against `transcript_schema.json`.

**Headline finding:** The dataset encodes a single dominant treatment-by-biomarker interaction. The therapeutic regimen is the conjunction of three binary indicators (`feature_001` AND `feature_014` AND `feature_021`) — none of the singletons or pairs help, but together they yield a 63% response (n=2,401, vs ~16% baseline; 3-way interaction coef +2.13, p=4e-92).

This treatment effect is completely abolished by either of two resistance markers. The complete favorable subgroup is `feature_001=1 AND feature_014=1 AND feature_021=1 AND feature_026=0 AND feature_009=0` (n=1,790, response 78.6% vs 16.5% in all other patients). `feature_026` and `feature_009` have no main effect in triple-negative patients — they are pure effect modifiers (interaction p < 1e-50 each). `feature_004` (a performance-status-like ordinal) and `feature_020` modulate response magnitude within the subgroup but do not abolish it.

